# Inv Ecosystem

## One-liner

An in-house investment platform that gives investors (LPs) a single authenticated place to view consolidated investment and portfolio data.

## Problem

Investment-related data is fragmented across sources. Inv Ecosystem should bring that data together so LPs can access what they need without switching tools or relying on ad-hoc reports.

## Audience

- **Primary:** Investors / LPs (limited partners)
- **Secondary:** TBD (internal team workflows may be added later)

## Core goals

1. Provide secure, login-only access for authorized investors
2. Consolidate investment and portfolio data in one application
3. Start with **accounts** as the first business domain after the app foundation
4. Deliver a Dutch-first UI with English planned later

## Non-goals (for now)

Not formally defined yet. Revisit as features are scoped.

## Current phase

**Foundation** — auth, dashboard shell, project conventions, and Cursor rules are in place. No business data or Supabase tables yet.

### Done

- Magic link auth (invite-only)
- Dashboard layout with sidebar
- Profile page shell
- i18n setup (Dutch primary)

### Next

- Accounts feature (first MVP business module)
- Supabase schema + generated types
- Business data models and UI

## Access & deployment

- Hosted online; **entire app requires authentication** (no public pages)
- Invite-only user access — users must exist in Supabase before login

## Stack

- Next.js 16 (App Router), React 19
- Supabase (auth + planned database)
- shadcn/ui, TanStack Query, next-intl
- TypeScript, Zod, React Hook Form

